text: Jo Dee Messina is an American country music artist. She was born in Massachusetts on August 25, 1970. She has had nine #1 songs on the United States Billboard Country Music Charts. As late as 2008 she had a song on Billboard's Hot Country Songs music chart. She has been honored under the Country Music Association. In the past, she was nominated for two Grammy Awards. She was the first female country artist to score 3 multiple-week number one singles. Messina relocated to Nashville, Tennessee around age 19. ==Discography== ;Studio albums * Jo Dee Messina (1996) * I'm Alright (1998) * Burn (2000) * Delicious Surprise (2005) * Me (2014) ==References== Category:1970 births Category:Living people Category:Singers from Massachusetts Category:American country singers Category:American singer- songwriters
